channel.title: Install on Wine error
channel.description:
Hello. I have Lubuntu 12.10 64bit and use Wine 1.4. After installation I get this message in the Terminal:
[code]osmodivs@Djiin:~/Public/BlackMesa$ wine BlackMesa-Setup.exe fixme :s hell:SHAutoComplete stub p11-kit: couldn't load module: /usr/lib/i386-linux-gnu/pkcs11/gnome-keyring-pkcs11.so: /usr/lib/i386-linux-gnu/pkcs11/gnome-keyring-pkcs11.so: cannot open shared object file: No such file or directory[/code]
How can I solve this problem so I can run BlackMesa?

item.title: Install on Wine error
item.dc:creator: sersoft
item.description:
If I’m not mistaken, gnome-keyring is like a password locker for settings and tasks that require root access, make sure you know your keyring password.

item.title: Install on Wine error
item.dc:creator: EccoBlackfin
item.description:
Osmodivs:

Hello.
I have Lubuntu 12.10 64bit and use Wine 1.4.
After installation I get this message in the Terminal:

osmodivs@Djiin:~/Public/BlackMesa$ wine BlackMesa-Setup.exe fixme :s hell:SHAutoComplete stub p11-kit: couldn't load module: /usr/lib/i386-linux-gnu/pkcs11/gnome-keyring-pkcs11.so: /usr/lib/i386-linux-gnu/pkcs11/gnome-keyring-pkcs11.so: cannot open shared object file: No such file or directory

How can I solve this problem so I can run BlackMesa?

Try this:
https://askubuntu.com/questions/127848/wine-cant-find-gnome-keyring-pkcs11-so

Basically it’s just complaining about not being able to find something, so of course, first make sure you have gnome-keyring installed.
